	<section class="specialties" id="specialties">
		<div class="container">
			<div class="heading text-center">
				<h2>Favourites</h2>
				<h3><br>Recommended Books -</br>

 

    <br>1.Srimad Bhagvad Gita (the "as it is" pocket book version) (A must-read for Success in the Spiritual as well as Materialistic world!)<br>
    2.Tao Te Ching by Lao Tzu (It's simple, yet very deep. Gives a clear perspective on the way to the ultimate truth.)<br>
    3.Flow: The Psychology of Optimal Experience by Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi (One of the best books that I have ever read!!!)<br>
    4.Unlimited Power by Anthony Robbins (Nice to get motivated and excited to do something.)<br>
    5.The Magic of Thinking Big by David J. Schwartz (Whether you think you can, or you think you can't, you're right!)<br>
    6.Think & Grow Rich by Napolean Hill (Undoubtedly, the best book ever written on becoming successful in the materialistic world!)<br>
    7.Marketing Management by Philip Kotler (For those who want to make it big in business.)<br>
    8.See You At The Top by Zig Ziglar (Full of real-life examples, inspirational stories and motivational quotes)<br>
    9.The Power of Now by Eckhart Tolle (Although I have read just a few pages of this book but I can say it with full confidence that this book has the power to change your life.)
    10.Rumi by Farrukh Dhondy (Heart-to-heart words.)<br>
    11.You can Heal Your Life by Louise L. Hay (The name says it all.)  <br>
    12.Power Pranayama by Dr. Renu Mahtani (Nothing compares to Pranayama when it comes to good health!)<br>
    13.The Supreme Yoga by Yoga Vasistha (Only for those who are at a very advanced state of consciousness.)<br>
    14.Avadhoot Gita in Hindi by Nandlal Dashora (Only for those who are at a very advanced state of consciousness.)<br>
    15.Ashtavakra Gita in Hindi by Nandlal Dashora (Only for those who are at a very advanced state of consciousness.)<br>
	16.Core of the Yoga Sutra by BKS Iyengar (To get an in-depth knowledge and understanding of "Ashtanga Yoga")<br>
	17.Krishna Niti by Dr. Girish P Jakhotiya (To enhance your leadership skills.)<br>
	18.Chicken Soup for the Unsinkable Soul (Short stories to make you smile and cry.)<br>
	19.Jonathan Livingston Seagull by Richard Bach (Get inspired for soaring to new heights.)<br>
	20.Gandhi on Personal Leadership by Anand Kumarasamy (To bring out the leader in you! )<br>
	21.How to Win Friends and Influence People by Dale Carnegie (The name says it all! )<br>
	22.The Power of Positive Thinking by Norman Vincent Peale (In a nutshell, our life depends upon our way of thinking.)<br>
	23.The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People by Stephen R. Covey (It's worth reading at least once.)<br>
	24.Who Moved My Cheese? by Spencer Johnson (One of my all-time favourites. I am sure you will love it too! )<br>
	25.The Alchemist by Paulo Coelho (Once you start reading it, you won't stop until you finish it!)<br>
</br>
<br>Recommended Videos -</br>

 

 <br>   1.Ramana Maharshi's English Audio Book on Self-Enquiry  (WHO AM I) ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=J2VcZWypI9c )<br>
    2.A Gift of Love (Heart Touching Rumi's Poetry) ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=X-idP23bHCg )<br>
    3.Biography of Dr. APJ Abdul Kalam Narrated By Gulzar Saab ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=OnGPHjuHEXE&list=PLD9C6176A59A44575 )<br>
    4.Dr Quantum - Double Slit Experiment ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=DfPeprQ7oGc )<br>
    5.Look at Yourself by Nick Vujicic ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=Gc4HGQHgeFE )<br>
    6.Steve Jobs' 2005 Stanford Commencement Address ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=UF8uR6Z6KLc )<br>
    7.Inspirational - How Great I Am ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=V6xLYt265ZM )<br>
    8.Randy Pausch Last Lecture: Achieving Your Childhood Dreams ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=ji5_MqicxSo )<br>
    9.Spiritual Reality: Power of Meditation (In English) ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=P1Dlsa8tbvU )<br>
    10.Spiritual Reality: Power of Meditation (In Hindi) ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=1DPKrKTRloQ )<br>
    11.Soul-Stirring Rumi's Poetry (In English) ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=4I60ZHdx5Og )<br>
    12.Jill Bolte Taylor's Stroke of Insight (in English) ( www.youtube.com/watch?v=UyyjU8fzEYU )</br>

 </h3>
